h1 Bonuses / modifiers

p Dexterity provides a modifier to the following actions:
  ul
    li <a href='/combat/base'>Base attack bonus</a> for ranged weapons
    li <a href='/def/ac'>Armor class</a>, specifically provides a Dexterity Bonus to AC
    li <a href='/def/ref'>Reflex saving throws</a>
    li <a href='http://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/acrobatics'>Acrobatics skill</a>
    li <a href='http://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/disable_device'>Disable Device skill</a>
    li <a href='http://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/escape_artist'>Escape Artist skill</a>
    li <a href='http://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/fly'>Fly skill</a>
    li <a href='http://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/ride'>Ride skill</a>
    li <a href='http://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/seight_of_hand'>Sleight of Hand skill</a>
    li <a href='http://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/stealth'>Stealth skill</a>

h1 Improving your Dexterity

p There are several avenues for improving this ability. The abilities within a category do not stack. You cannot have two enhancement bonuses active at once, only the largest bonus takes effect.

p In general, magical items are the easiest way to start boosting your stats.

p Note that every two points of ability improvement provides a one point modifier to the relevant abilities listed above.

